SIMPLE: eleventh
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eleventh
<hw>E*lev"enth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS.
<ets>endlyfta</ets>. See <er>Eleven</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Next
after the tenth; <as>as, the <ex>eleventh</ex> chapter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Constituting one of eleven parts into which a thing
is divided; <as>as, the <ex>eleventh</ex> part of a
thing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the interval
of the octave and the fourth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eleventh</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eleventh
<hw>E*lev"enth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quotient of a
unit divided by eleven; one of eleven equal parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The interval consisting of ten
conjunct degrees; the interval made up of an octave and a
fourth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elf</ent>⟦br⟧
